Encode data for getting a JWT token

This takes in options for stuff such as secret
Data is read from the output

Example:
  echo '{"Hello": "World"}' | ./jwt-cli encode --secret SECRET

Usage:
  ./jwt-cli encode [flags]

Aliases:
  encode, e

Flags:
  -d, --data string          the claims to be signed. Using @- will read the data from stdin (default "@-")
  -h, --help                 help for encode
  -s, --secret string        the secret needed
  -m, --sign-method string   the signing method (default "H256")
